Three people died and five others were injuries in a clash between police and Lessos residents in Nandi County. The locals engaged the police in running battles following the shooting death of a cobbler as officers were enforcing Covid-19 regulations. Residents claimed police shot and killed the physically challenged cobbler as he confronted them for harassing a boda boda rider. Chaos erupted after dozens of villagers stormed Lessos Police Station and set ablaze the house of the OCS. They were protesting the death of the cobbler and the alleged harassment of boda boda riders by police. The locals claimed police officers were demanding Sh50 bribe from the riders for not wearing face masks. The angry residents clashed with security officers for more than two hours accusing them of using brutal force. Five people were injured during the fracas and were taken to Kapsabet Hospital. More follows.